Most personal cars sit quietly at the curb or in a garage for 95% of the day, so why even have one?
With transportation — mostly passenger vehicles — responsible for about 40% of the state’s greenhouse-gas emissions, policymakers are ramping up efforts to uncouple Californians from their cars.
One of the things those commercials don’t say: Cars cost nearly $10,000 a year to operate in California, more if you have an older one.
